{"type": "article", "id": 34506, "title": "像画画一样给食物上油｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2016-11-15T23:14:10Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 30564, "name": "OTOTO"}, {"id": 34900, "name": "Firebox"}, {"id": 571, "name": "Autodesk"}, {"id": 34901, "name": "Elliot Bastianon"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 4, "praise_count": 160, "image": "img/article/article_show/20161115210236aELyvO8I65G9oi0K.jpg", "contents": "<p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Kitt-a-Boo Wall Hook by Firebox</h3><p>总有一些有趣的小物能给你的生活注入惊喜，英国创意购物网站 <a href=\"https://www.firebox.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Firebox</a> 最近推出的 Kitt-a-Boo 挂钩就是其中之一。平时它是一个看上去不起眼的小盒子，一旦你把东西挂在钩子上，你就会“惊动”盒子里的小猫，提醒你别乱动它的“尾巴”。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.firebox.com/Kitt-a-Boo-Wall-Hook/p7834\" rel=\"nofollow\">预订链接</a>，售价为 16.89 英镑。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210320eBsRWd4AX8imHZgp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210320D45XomHn2JlCQfct.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210326pQxZXBPnC5yDEWFh.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bixi by Bluemint Labs</h3><p>不想用脏手触摸设备的时候，你是不是也幻想过像科幻片中的角色那样，在设备上方做个手势就能进行相应的操作？最近来自美国的设计团队 Bluemint Labs 就打造了一款小巧的手势遥控器 Bixi，这个名字来源于中国古代传说中名为赑屃的神兽，形似乌龟。通过内置的传感器，它可以识别到各种不同的手势。使用前需要通过蓝牙与手机相连，再利用配套的应用连接到其他智能设备进行操控。它对设备最远的支持距离为 25 米，不过在有墙壁遮挡的情况下会相应缩短。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1860920533/bixi-control-any-smart-device-by-simply-waving-you\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>参与众筹，最低价为 79 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210632Yqzb0wWIlvH3D8xE.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563333\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210636HiXs8BvUdFbrOtWK.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563333\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210347H2hDtPCcGjUqNSy7.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.669118\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210347oWwN6M2p5LYBCx3I.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.239706\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Mark-Eat! by Lior Rokah-Kor</h3><p>来自以色列的创意工作室 <a href=\"http://www.ototodesign.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">OTOTO</a> 总能带来让你眼前一亮的产品，设计师 Lior Rokah-Kor 就对常用的厨具油刷进行了一次改造。Mark-Eat! 看上去就像是一支马克笔，使用时只要把刷头放入油中，轻挤笔身就能把油吸进去了，之后你就能像画画一样处理食材。这是它的<a href=\"http://www.ototodesign.com/collections/all-products/products/mark-eat-basting-brush-pump\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 16 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210434m6c7YotZbMuiCdIQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.675676\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210433vdUZbXRHAgt9NK2Y.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.675676\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210433o5aUQkudXtAFHze3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210433QO8sJMGhzIP9xlWg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Unexpected Collection by Elliot Bastianon</h3><p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>澳大利亚设计师 <a href=\"http://www.elliotbastianon.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Elliot Bastianon</a> 热衷于探索非常规材料在家具设计上的应用，最近他尝试将 <a href=\"http://kireiusa.com/echopanel-acoustics/\" rel=\"nofollow\">EchoPanel</a> 的吸音板制作成各种有着独特造型的家具。在这套名为 Unexpected Collection 的系列中，Bastianon 运用折叠、弯曲等加工方式将吸音板同木料巧妙地融合在了一起。目前这个系列囊括了咖啡桌、长椅、置物架以及吊灯。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210509Xi6yhNLUb9odDz0C.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.653125\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201611152105083eEqsvMjAbZpTK1c.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210509sVdikSIureo9H3wg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.715741\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210508iv4YaPKfEeyXm5bg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.723148\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210508bGYEWvZ19Rpy8sK0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><h3>Elbo Chair by Autodesk</h3><p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>美国软件制作公司 <a href=\"http://www.autodesk.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Autodesk</a> 旗下生成设计实验室的两位设计师联手制作了一把具有骨感美的椅子。为了制作这把名为 <a href=\"https://gallery.autodesk.com/fusion360/projects/68792/elbo-chair--generated-in-project-dreamcatcher-made-with-fusion-360\" rel=\"nofollow\">Elbo</a> 的木制椅子，设计师们将大量普通人坐在椅子上的状态数据导入了公司的 Dreamcatcher 软件内，从而得出了椅子所需的连接点的数量。随后他们再根据模拟出的造型，采用数控雕刻机（CNC Router）对木材进行加工。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232538RdFoqbT4ilUtzJBO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232537V860GFRczJiej5Wy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232538YKAbyJ4G2kLPUaOd.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232537aytNcojOr5RHsefY.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232537Rs82jMeuPXZnpvGV.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115232538pyJM0QrTGSvdE7Ue.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Habibi by Kim Ramain-Colomb</h3><p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>瑞士洛桑艺术与设计大学（ECAL）的 Kim Ramain-Colomb 以摩洛哥的传统化妆品为灵感，设计了一套名为 Habibi 的概念化妆品包装。盛放化妆品的是一个个几何造型的陶器，Ramain-Colomb 为它们设计的保护措施是模仿手机滑动解锁的纸质抽屉，排版和颜色正好和化妆品的一一对应，让打开的过程显得相当奇妙。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210558AC6VcPKyM0sj47iD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562606\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210558nrzNed3G4bj2YyZA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210603WvsitFrEXghHO5Ua.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.333333\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161115210559BobcvQ5iJILkzGf1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}